.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093841/Thomson-Piedmont-gravel-ti-frame-rear-triangle-dropouts-brake-mount-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093841/Thomson-Piedmont-gravel-ti-frame-rear-triangle-dropouts-brake-mount-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093841/Thomson-Piedmont-gravel-ti-frame-rear-triangle-dropouts-brake-mount-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093841/Thomson-Piedmont-gravel-ti-frame-rear-triangle-dropouts-brake-mount-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093841/Thomson-Piedmont-gravel-ti-frame-rear-triangle-dropouts-brake-mount-1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261810\">The Piedmont runs a 12mm thru-ale and flat mount brakes</figcaption></figure><p>The titanium frameset is available in five stock sizes from XS-XL with reach spanning a 374mm to 410mm range. Standard 12mm x 148mm rear end spacing and 428mm chainstays give rise to sufficient clearance for 700c x 44c tires; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/09/19/thomson-titanium-from-seatposts-to-gravel-mtb-frames-plus-matte-carbon/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">see the bike here</a> with Vredestein’s 44mm gravel tire.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093853/Thomson-Piedmont-titanium-gravel-frame-downtube-bottle-bosses.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14093853/Thomson-Piedmont-titanium-gravel-frame-downtube-bottle-bosses.jpg\" alt=\"thomson piedmont downtube internal cable routing bottle bosses\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bi